</BLOCKQUOTE><BR>While I agree with Frodlin that it is unlikely the case that it was too powerful, it isn't unheard for SOE to do something like this, and for too long.&nbsp; Again I'm not remotely claiming that it was too powerful, but that the possibility exists, nothing more nothing less.&nbsp; Frankly BoD was too powerful for where it dropped.&nbsp; I haven't seen anything drop in single group content since then that compares to it's overall power in the forms of DPS and agro. (I'm one of those paladins that prefers agro on my weapon to DPS, or even heal procs).&nbsp;&nbsp; That is basically what led me to that line of thinking, that instead of bringing out the nerf bat, which always starts a riot SOE has been known to just let things stagnate, and while unlikely the possibility can't be completely discarded.&nbsp; The overriding point to this premise is that the stagnation has gone on too long...another SOE trait.
				
